Visited this place for the first time a few weeks ago. It's surprisingly a hidden gem in the area that I've driven by and walked by many times without going in. I'm glad I finally went in and dined there because it was excellent! The service was excellent and the servers were super sweet. They made us feel right at home. The foods was amazing. We had a house salad, a cheeseburger, and a small pizza. The portions were huge and the burger I had was mouth-watering and tender. The pizza was cooked perfectly and had a perfect balance of sauce, crust, and cheese. If you're looking for a quick lunch spot or a casual take-out dinner, definitely check this place out!
